WorkItem.ClosedComment:
The lib.d.ts we ship is based on the features supported by IE 11, since IE doesn't support the message property we've not included that.

As a workaround, you can re-open the interface in your application and add the message property.

````
interface DOMError{
     message : string;
}
````

We will add this property when IE supports it.

WorkItem.Description:
Currently DOMError interface is defined as:
```
interface DOMError {
    name: string;
    toString(): string;
}
```

According to this spec: http://www.w3.org/TR/dom/#interface-domerror it also has a message property.
